   <concept id="FAR_25_1001" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">25.1001</ph> Waiver of right to
examination of records.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1672e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Policy</i>. The clause at <xref href="52.215-2.dita#FAR_52_215_2"
                        base="i1059150"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.215-2</xref>, Audit and Records-Negotiation, prescribed at <xref href="15.209.dita#FAR_15_209"
                        base="i1109112"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15.209</xref>(b), and paragraph (d) of the clause at <xref href="52.212-5.dita#FAR_52_212_5"
                        base="i1061237"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.212-5</xref>, Contract Terms and Conditions Required to Implement Statutes or Executive Orders-Commercial Products and Commercial Services, prescribed at <xref href="12.301.dita#FAR_12_301"
                        base="i1113145"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">12.301</xref>(b)(4), implement 
                     <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3841&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3841</xref>
                     
                   and 41 U.S.C. 4706. The basic clauses authorize examination of records by the Comptroller General.</p>
               <ol id="d1672e45" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e37">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Insert the appropriate basic clause,
whenever possible, in negotiated contracts with foreign contractors.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e42">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The contracting
officer may use <xref href="52.215-2.dita#FAR_52_215_2"
                              base="i1059150"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.215-2</xref> with
its Alternate III or <xref href="52.212-5.dita#FAR_52_212_5"
                              base="i1061237"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-5</xref> with
its Alternate I after-</p>
                     <ol id="d1672e70" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e54">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Exhausting all reasonable efforts
to include the basic clause;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e59">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Considering
factors such as alternate sources of supply, additional cost, and
time of delivery; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e64">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> The head
of the agency has executed a determination and findings in accordance
with paragraph (b) of this section, with the concurrence of the
Comptroller General. However, concurrence of the Comptroller General
is not required if the contractor is a foreign government or agency
thereof or is precluded by the laws of the country involved from
making its records available for examination.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e69">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Determination
and findings</i>. The determination and findings must-</p>
               <ol id="d1672e114" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e77">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Identify
the contract and its purpose, and identify if the contract is with
a foreign contractor or with a foreign government or an agency of
a foreign government;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e82">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Describe
the efforts to include the basic clause;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e87">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> State the
reasons for the contractor’s refusal to include the basic clause;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e92">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Describe
the price and availability of the supplies or services from the
United States and other sources; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1694e97">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph> Determine
that it will best serve the interest of the United States to use
the appropriate alternate clause in paragraph (a)(2) of this section.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
